Andrew J. Silverberg Joins Mark Asset Management Corp. as Partner and Executive Vice President | Business Wire


























































Andrew J. Silverberg Joins Mark Asset Management Corp. as Partner and 
      Executive Vice President






April 03, 2012 07:30 AM Eastern Daylight Time



NEW YORK--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Mark Asset Management Corp. today announced that Andrew J. Silverberg 
      has joined the firm as an Executive Vice President and Partner, 
      returning to the firm where he began his highly successful investing 
      career. Mr. Silverberg, 34, will join Mark Asset Management’s Founder 
      and President Morris Mark in managing all the firm’s hedge funds and 
      will be directly involved in the expansion of its Investment Focus Fund, 
      and its Growth and Income Fund.
    


      Mark Asset Management, which is a registered investment advisor, manages 
      Mark Partners and Mark International Partners, and separately manages 
      accounts for institutions, families, and other high net worth investors.
    

      Morris Mark commented on Mr. Silverberg’s appointment, saying: “I am 
      thrilled to have Andrew rejoining us. I have known him as both a friend 
      and a colleague since 1999, and I could not be more pleased to see him 
      return to the company where he began his investing career. He is a 
      top-notch investment professional who will help bolster our team and 
      expand our offerings.”
    

      Mr. Silverberg brings more than a decade of investment experience to 
      Mark Asset Management, where he began his investment career in 1999. In 
      2001, Andrew joined money management firm, Fred Alger Management. After 
      a series of promotions, he was made Senior Vice President and Portfolio 
      Manager of the Company’s Large Cap Growth and Growth and Income 
      portfolios, and in addition, the equity portion of Alger’s Balanced 
      portfolio.
    

      “This is a very exciting time to be re-joining Morris and his team,” Mr. 
      Silverberg said. “I started my career with Morris, and was able to 
      develop my skills working alongside one of the industry’s very best. 
      Now, 13 years later, I could not be happier to be Morris’s partner, 
      working with him again as we take the opportunity presented by a great 
      environment to expand upon his success for our investors.”
    

      Mr. Silverberg graduated from Brooklyn College with a BS in Business, 
      Management and Finance. He was a member of the Scholars Program at 
      Brooklyn College, the Phi Beta Kappa Society, and was a winner of the T. 
      Bruce Birkenhead Prize in Economics.
    

About Mark Asset Management


      Mark Asset Management Corporation manages two investment-oriented hedge 
      funds, Mark Partners and Mark International Partners, and directly 
      manages separate accounts for individual and institutional clients. The 
      firm, established in 1985, has generated excellent returns by utilizing 
      fundamental research with a primary objective of significant long term 
      capital appreciation. Among Mark Asset's clients are pension funds, 
      individuals, families, charitable foundations and educational endowments.
    


